name: NoSuchFieldError
comment:
Thrown if an application tries to access or modify a specified field of an object, and that object no longer has that field.

Normally, this error is caught by the compiler; this error can only occur at run time if the definition of a class has incompatibly changed.

constructors.name: NoSuchFieldError
constructors.comment: Constructs a NoSuchFieldError with no detail message.

constructors.name: NoSuchFieldError
constructors.comment: Constructs a NoSuchFieldError with the specified detail message.
